            "metadata": {},
            "source": "## B.Data Description\n"
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": "### B.1.Data acquisition "
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": "The Data provided by Seattle Police Department  and  Traffic Records department from 2004 to Present, in total there are 37 attribute (independent variables ) , The dependent variable (SEVERITYCODE) contains numbers of the correspond to different level of severity caused by accident from 0 to 4 , are as follows:\n\n 0: Little to no Probability (Clear Condition)\\   \n \n 1: very low probability (Chance or property damage)\\  \n \n 2: low probability (Chance of injury)\\  \n \n 3: Mid probability (Chance of serious injury)\\  \n \n 4: High probability (Chance of fatality)\\  \n \nSome attribute have missing data, have numerical and categorical types of data need for preprocessing before any future processing.\n"
        },
        {
